content:
Run a dataflow for the first time to create the datasets it defines. Run it again to update the dataset with the latest synced data.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

To run a dataflow: 
Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows
Click Data Manager in the left pane to open Data Manager.
Click the Dataflows & Recipes tab.
Click the triangle  to the right of the dataflow you want to run, and select Run Now.
The dataflow job is added to the job queue. After the job completes, CRM Analytics sends an email notification to the user who created the dataflow.

If a dataflow job fails, click  next to the job status to stop it.
A stopped dataflow job can be restarted by clicking Start, but it will start over from the beginning.
You can monitor a dataflow job on the Monitor tab and refresh the CRM Analytics home page after the job completes successfully.
title: Running Dataflows in Salesforce
